Demonstrate Association rule generation on credit card data using apriori algorithm.
Aim: To generate association rules from a transaction dataset using the Apriori algorithm in WEKA
and identify relationships among items frequently purchased together.
Tools Used:
 WEKA (Waikato Environment for Knowledge Analysis)
 Supermarket dataset (built-in transaction dataset in WEKA)
Dataset Used:
 Supermarket.arff, included in WEKA installation.
 Each row represents a transaction, and columns represent items purchased
 (nominal attributes: true/false).
Date: Roll No.:
 Data Mining Page No.: 36
Procedure:
Step 1: Load Dataset
1. Open WEKA Explorer.
2. Go to the Preprocess tab.
3. Click Open file and select supermarket.arff.
Step 2: Set Up Apriori Algorithm
1. Switch to the Associate tab.
2. Select the Apriori algorithm.
3. Configure parameters:
o Minimum Support: 0.1 (10%)
o Minimum Confidence: 0.6 (60%)
o Number of Rules: 10

Date: Roll No.:
 Data Mining Page No.: 37
Step 3: Run Apriori Algorithm
1. Click Start to execute the algorithm and generate association rules.
2. WEKA will display frequent itemsets along with their support and confidence values.
3. The top rules are automatically ranked based on confidence.

Step 4: Analyze Rules
1. Observe the frequent itemsets and rules in the Result Panel.
2. Each rule shows:
o Support: Frequency of the itemset in the dataset.
o Confidence: Likelihood of the consequent given the antecedent.
3. Identify the strongest rules with high support and confidence for practical insights.
4. Compare rules to detect unexpected patterns that may reveal new business opportunities.
Step 5: Interpretation
1. The rules reveal patterns of items bought together.
2. Useful for cross-selling, promotions, and marketing strategies.
3. Helps in planning store layout by placing frequently bought items nearby.
4. Can be used to design combo offers and discounts to increase sales and customer satisfaction.
