Conclusion:
The Apriori algorithm in WEKA successfully generates association rules from the transaction
dataset, identifying frequent item combinations and relationships among items purchased together.
Using the Supermarket dataset, which simulates credit card transactions, we can observe patterns in
customer purchasing behavior. These association rules provide valuable insights for business
decisions such as product placement, cross-selling, and targeted marketing strategies. WEKA makes
it easy to mine, visualize, and interpret these rules efficiently, demonstrating the practical application
of association rule mining in real-world transactional data.
